Conflict-free Replicated Data Types (CRDTs)

   Nuno Preguiça ^1 Carlos Baquero ^2 Marc Shapiro ^3 (BUTTON) Détails
   1 NOVA-LINCS - NOVA Laboratory for Computer Science and Informatics
   2 Universidade do Minho
   3 DELYS - DistributEd aLgorithms and sYStems
   Inria de Paris, LIP6

       Nuno Preguiça ^1 AuthorId : 1385058
     Auteur

       Carlos Baquero ^2 AuthorId : 769238
     Auteur Etablissement employeur : Universidade do Minho

       Marc Shapiro ^3 AuthorId : 97976
     Auteur Etablissement employeur : Institut National de Recherche en
     Informatique et en Automatique IdHAL : shapiro

   1 NOVA-LINCS - NOVA Laboratory for Computer Science and Informatics
   (Portugal) StructId : 420636
     * NOVA - Universidade Nova de Lisboa (Campus de Campolide 1099-085
       Lisboa - Portugal) StructId : 327246

   2 Universidade do Minho (Largo do Paço, 4704-553 Braga - Portugal)
   StructId : 300854
   3 DELYS - DistributEd aLgorithms and sYStems (2 rue Simone Iff -CS
   42112 -75589 Paris Cedex 12 - France) StructId : 541722
     * Inria de Paris (2 rue Simone Iff - CS 42112 - 75589 Paris Cedex 12
       - France) StructId : 454310
          + Inria - Institut National de Recherche en Informatique et en
            Automatique (Domaine de Voluceau Rocquencourt - BP 105 78153
            Le Chesnay Cedex - France) StructId : 300009
     * LIP6 (4 Place JUSSIEU 75252 PARIS CEDEX 05 - France) StructId :
       541703
          + SU - Sorbonne Université (21 rue de l’École de médecine -
            75006 Paris - France) StructId : 413221
          + CNRS - Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique : UMR7606
            (France) StructId : 441569

   (BUTTON) Masquer les détails
   Abstract : A conflict-free replicated data type (CRDT) is an abstract
   data type, with a well defined interface, designed to be replicated at
   multiple processes and exhibiting the following properties: (1) any
   replica can be modified without coordinating with another replicas; (2)
   when any two replicas have received the same set of updates, they reach
   the same state, deterministically, by adopting mathematically sound
   rules to guarantee state convergence.
   Keywords : Eventual consistency Consistency Distributed computing
   Causal consistency Data replication
   Type de document :
   Chapitre d'ouvrage
   Domaine :

   Informatique [cs] / Calcul parallèle, distribué et partagé [cs.DC]

   Liste complète des métadonnées (BUTTON)  Voir (BUTTON)  Masquer
